419
00:31:32,811 --> 00:31:35,848
We should take out the
36383 outta Stage Harbor.

420
00:31:36,063 --> 00:31:38,926
Takes a little...sure.
But atleast you'll be able to get out.

421
00:31:47,986 --> 00:31:49,608
Godspeed, Chief.

422
00:31:50,414 --> 00:31:54,079
Let Gouthro Livesey down the fishing pier.
Yes, sir.

423
00:33:08,392 --> 00:33:11,521
Don't get me sick, Gus.
You should't even be out here.

424
00:33:11,687 --> 00:33:13,890
Why you always dragging us, Richie?

425
00:33:13,914 --> 00:33:16,168
Don't take it out on us just 'cause
you ain't rollin' with Bangs.

426
00:33:16,236 --> 00:33:19,115
Atleast we'll get out!
We won't, screw you! That was a year ago!

427
00:33:19,282 --> 00:33:20,324
Screw you!?

428
00:33:20,491 --> 00:33:23,621
No one could have got over the bar that day.
Bangs did it.

429
00:33:23,788 --> 00:33:26,917
Oh! Really, Richie?
He's not trying to get across the bar today!

430
00:33:27,251 --> 00:33:31,131
No, he says take the 36383 right off
from the nice protected bay site.

431
00:33:31,231 --> 00:33:32,331
Ah!

432
00:33:36,555 --> 00:33:39,350
Bernie, it doesn't matter what Richie thinks...

433
00:33:40,101 --> 00:33:43,481
Bangs or whoever thinks. Nobody.

434
00:33:44,232 --> 00:33:47,278
No one could have saved those men at the Langery.

435
00:33:48,071 --> 00:33:52,535
Sometimes you know...men die, Bernie.

436
00:34:25,412 --> 00:34:27,290
Alright, here we go.

437
00:34:32,130 --> 00:34:34,550
Alright, hang on.
Now, easy fellas.

438
00:34:34,717 --> 00:34:37,101
Got it.
Ok, now up, up, up, up.

439
00:34:37,679 --> 00:34:42,603
One, two...all together now.

440
00:34:46,358 --> 00:34:47,359
Three.

441
00:34:52,158 --> 00:34:53,923
Nicely done boys!
Now tie it.

442
00:34:53,993 --> 00:34:57,205
Alright! Now we got a tiller.
Now we gonna drive her in a shore.

443
00:34:57,373 --> 00:35:01,065
Ah! Ah! Brown and them others are getting
ready to rise some lifeboats.

444
00:35:01,085 --> 00:35:02,845
They think it's their best hope.

445
00:35:02,945 --> 00:35:04,845
Oh, Pop!

446
00:35:06,218 --> 00:35:10,265
We need every guy we got!
Well...they're gonna grab those lifeboats.

447
00:35:41,474 --> 00:35:43,894
What are you trying to do, Sybert?
Get off of him.

448
00:35:46,731 --> 00:35:49,110
You trying to kill us?
You trying to kill us?

449
00:35:49,276 --> 00:35:51,863
Take it easy.
Stand up.

450
00:35:52,030 --> 00:35:55,034
You're outta your mind!
He just saved your life.

451
00:35:55,201 --> 00:35:58,831
The boat is in pieces.
It's gone, enough!

452
00:36:03,337 --> 00:36:05,757
That boat is too small for this seas.

453
00:36:05,923 --> 00:36:10,430
And this boat will be sunk by night fall.

454
00:36:10,597 --> 00:36:11,932
Every fellar who wants to live...

455
00:36:12,099 --> 00:36:16,146
and the only way that happens
is if we run her run aground.

456
00:36:18,900 --> 00:36:22,363
We setup a watch and look out for a shore.

457
00:36:22,530 --> 00:36:25,325
I need four men working the pulleys
on the emergency tiller.

458
00:36:25,492 --> 00:36:28,288
I need four men manning the pump,
aft the steerin'...

459
00:36:28,454 --> 00:36:31,292
and the rest of you bucket top side below...

460
00:36:31,458 --> 00:36:33,503
and communicates with the engine room.

461
00:36:34,671 --> 00:36:40,054
And somebody...keep blowing that whistle.

462
00:36:40,220 --> 00:36:42,974
You heard him, boys.
Now move it! Come on!

463
00:36:47,772 --> 00:36:50,108
Sounds like you're the man now, Sybert.

464
00:36:52,737 --> 00:36:55,533
Hope you just didn't kill us all.

465
00:37:13,933 --> 00:37:16,979
I saw a ship driftin'.
Heard it whistle.

466
00:37:17,145 --> 00:37:20,108
A distress signal.
45 minutes ago, Bernie.

467
00:37:20,274 --> 00:37:21,276
From my house!

468
00:37:24,071 --> 00:37:27,075
Ah! The wind's blowin' south,
and those currents, I...

469
00:37:28,035 --> 00:37:31,631
I guess that'll put up here
about comin' near over the bar.

470
00:37:31,957 --> 00:37:34,002
Can't be part of the Mercer, Bernie.

471
00:37:34,168 --> 00:37:35,795
She's off Nantucket, 40 miles...

472
00:37:35,962 --> 00:37:38,358
means she would've drifted northwest, right?

473
00:37:38,424 --> 00:37:43,055
I know what I heard.
Know what I saw.

474
00:37:47,478 --> 00:37:48,605
