01:11:19,349 --> 01:11:20,909
Brace yourselves!

707
01:11:34,196 --> 01:11:36,907
It's really nice here.

708
01:11:44,497 --> 01:11:48,917
Take it, use it.
Consider it done.

709
01:11:55,521 --> 01:11:56,982
What's wrong with it!?
We lost the pumps.

710
01:11:57,049 --> 01:12:00,469
The pumps are chokin' the breakers.
Go check the connections.

711
01:12:02,972 --> 01:12:04,181
Give me the light.

712
01:12:05,557 --> 01:12:10,061
It's onet of those damn...
Sometimes I wish I didn't understand.

713
01:12:11,270 --> 01:12:13,064
Sybert, what's goin' on?

714
01:12:15,023 --> 01:12:17,067
We're usin' every pump we got.

715
01:12:18,026 --> 01:12:20,762
The jam the breakers and
the pumps wouldn't trickle.

716
01:12:20,828 --> 01:12:25,241
We got another two feet of water before it hits
the air in engine and then the ship's dead.

717
01:12:25,407 --> 01:12:27,844
Jesus Christ.
Do you hear that?

718
01:12:27,910 --> 01:12:33,131
The tide's rising workin' us up the shole.
Fellas, that give us some time.

719
01:12:33,832 --> 01:12:36,917
Isn't that right, Mr.Sybert?
That's sure, is Bub.

720
01:12:37,877 --> 01:12:40,796
As long as the generators keep the pumps goin'.

721
01:12:42,506 --> 01:12:44,649
By however we buy some more time.

722
01:12:44,716 --> 01:12:46,926
You wanna be to be the man, Sybert right?
Well now you are the man.

723
01:12:47,677 --> 01:12:50,179
You got no wife, got no kids back home?

724
01:12:51,848 --> 01:12:56,935
You're a single man always hidin' down below.
What do you gotta lose?

725
01:12:57,102 --> 01:12:58,386
Enough, Brown.

726
01:13:01,148 --> 01:13:03,107
I'm afraid, Brown.

727
01:13:04,401 --> 01:13:06,193
Gotta a life, same as you.

728
01:13:11,031 --> 01:13:13,825
Just don't see sittin' around,
talkin' about it.

729
01:13:18,371 --> 01:13:23,684
Station Chatham, 36500.
Station Chatham, 36500, do you copy?

730
01:13:23,751 --> 01:13:28,454
Station Chatham,
this is Chief Bangs, CG-36383,

731
01:13:28,505 --> 01:13:33,342
Pollock lightship, CG-36500, do you copy?

732
01:13:33,717 --> 01:13:36,929
Why can't they hear us, Bernie?
We hear them.

733
01:13:37,095 --> 01:13:41,299
Tide is too high, zero head way.
Station Chatham, do you copy?

734
01:13:41,391 --> 01:13:42,985
I repeat, we're comin' home.

735
01:13:43,051 --> 01:13:46,696
Station Chatham, 36383,
return to Old Harbor.

736
01:13:46,963 --> 01:13:50,316
Pollock lightship, CG-36500, do you copy?

737
01:13:50,482 --> 01:13:52,150
We are all alone.

738
01:13:52,943 --> 01:13:55,768
You heard, Bangs, on the Radio like he's
out goin' all back in but couldn't get out...

739
01:13:55,795 --> 01:13:58,723
and the storm's gets worse...

740
01:14:00,240 --> 01:14:02,009
We must return back, Webber.

741
01:14:02,577 --> 01:14:06,613
We've come farther than anybody
ever thought possible, Bernie!

742
01:14:07,456 --> 01:14:11,918
Maybe Richie is right!
Maybe we should just go back!

743
01:14:12,085 --> 01:14:18,423
The wind is eight to nine.
Repeat, Wind eight to nine. Heavy snowfall.

744
01:14:18,591 --> 01:14:20,333
You heard Bangs on the radio.

745
01:14:20,467 --> 01:14:23,428
We have no compass and
we have no way to communicate.

746
01:14:26,981 --> 01:14:30,976
You are...
What? What? I'm what Ritchie?

747
01:14:32,460 --> 01:14:38,191
I got us this far, didn't I?
Not Bangs not Cluff, but I did it!

748
01:14:44,738 --> 01:14:46,240
We did it, Richie.

749
01:14:50,159 --> 01:14:51,745
You wanna turn back around?

750
01:14:53,997 --> 01:14:57,299
No, not now! We came too far.

751
01:14:58,000 --> 01:14:59,668
We are not gonna leave 'em.

752
01:15:02,295 --> 01:15:04,130
Not on my watch.

753
01:15:06,633 --> 01:15:08,009
Just do your job.

754
01:15:12,429 --> 01:15:15,515
Hey Fitz, turn off the beam.
We'll work in the dark.

755
01:15:15,682 --> 01:15:19,018
We can see the light of the
Pendleton better in the dark.

756
01:15:26,858 --> 01:15:28,235
Watch it.

757
01:15:34,198 --> 01:15:35,441
Get back here.

758
01:15:37,701 --> 01:15:39,086
Get your buds back here.

759
01:15:39,912 --> 01:15:41,955
I lost my hat.

760
01:16:07,644 --> 01:16:08,953
You okay?

761
01:16:10,855 --> 01:16:16,694
Yeah, I'm just tired.
Come on.

762
01:16:21,406 --> 01:16:23,366
You kids go play in the bedroom, ok?

763
01:16:23,633 --> 01:16:25,777
You can wait.
Let me call my brother.

764
01:16:25,797 --> 01:16:28,688
Thanks. Call me Mariam.

765
01:16:46,003 --> 01:16:48,380
You think your mother would
mind if I turn on the radio?

766
01:16:55,478 --> 01:16:58,314
Coast Boston, this is the Unimak.

767
01:16:58,481 --> 01:17:01,558
We are first at the Mercer bow
her now at the Port of Yakutat.

768
01:17:01,624 --> 01:17:05,378
Four Mercer crew members jumped from the deck.
All are lost.

769
01:17:05,445 --> 01:17:09,866
I repeat, four men lost.
Several crew members have hypothermia.

770
01:17:10,032 --> 01:17:14,119
We'll wait for daybreak to attempt another rescue.
Over.

771
01:17:15,996 --> 01:17:20,658
Does no good listenin' to all that chatter, Mariam.
Better to live not knowin'.

772
01:17:25,552 --> 01:17:27,552
...it would be 1900 hours...

773
01:17:32,552 --> 01:17:35,554
How long have you been married to Bernie for?
We are...

774
01:17:40,308 --> 01:17:42,269
We're not married yet.

775
01:17:44,729 --> 01:17:48,015
I didn't know if...
Like I said, Bernie is a good man.

776
01:17:52,236 --> 01:17:56,573
Him and some of them others try gettin' out one year ago saved my husband Arnie and the crew of the Landry.

777
01:17:56,948 --> 01:18:00,285
They were out on the boat night time off
Nantucket when the boat started takin' water.

778
01:18:00,451 --> 01:18:02,203
A night just like this.

779
01:18:03,413 --> 01:18:06,165
Come on, we gotta get goin'.

780
01:18:06,331 --> 01:18:09,576
Brother's on his way to come meet us.
I gotta get to the lodge, come on, you two.

781
01:18:43,167 --> 01:18:47,881
because people said sit down sit down,
let you rock the boat 753

782
01:18:49,215 --> 01:18:54,013
* Cause people said sit, down sit down *
* you rock the boat *

783
01:18:54,180 --> 01:18:59,812
* the devil you can pull down *
* the sharp edges of your jacket *

784
01:19:09,614 --> 01:19:11,375
* Sit down, sit down, sit down *

785
01:19:55,694 --> 01:19:57,137
Do you know who she is?

786
01:19:58,214 --> 01:20:02,335
Ain't Bernie's fault, Carlin.
No one's fault. It's like her blaming you.

787
01:20:03,387 --> 01:20:04,680
For what?

788
01:20:04,847 --> 01:20:08,159
You are the one that told me there was no
other ship out there because of you, right?

789
01:21:25,317 --> 01:21:28,153
Fitz, turn on the searchlight.

790
01:22:16,920 --> 01:22:19,398
I can't believe we found her.
Look at that!

791
01:22:23,678 --> 01:22:27,558
We're too late.
It's a ghost ship.

792
01:22:31,946 --> 01:22:34,101
Are you seeing this, sir?
Yeah.

793
01:22:34,201 --> 01:22:36,901
Yeah, yeah...I see him.

794
01:22:36,777 --> 01:22:38,529
Not sure I believe it!

795
01:22:41,782 --> 01:22:43,952
Where is the hell's he goin'?

796
01:22:52,337 --> 01:22:53,922
Good to see you boys.

797
01:23:00,728 --> 01:23:02,228
Careful.

798
01:23:08,982 --> 01:23:14,154
How are we gonna fit them all on this boat?
We were told to fit only 12, including us.

799
01:23:15,665 --> 01:23:17,367
Those are just regulation, right?

800
01:23:21,872 --> 01:23:23,415
How many could you fit?

801
01:23:24,917 --> 01:23:26,502
20, 22 tops.

802
01:23:29,131 --> 01:23:30,298
Wait.

803
01:23:30,465 --> 01:23:32,134
They comin' out here.

804
01:23:56,296 --> 01:23:58,173
Try the station, Port side.

805
01:24:28,617 --> 01:24:30,578
Come on, I got you.

806
01:24:51,311 --> 01:24:52,512
We got ya.

807
01:25:02,282 --> 01:25:03,658
Maske, get over here!

808
01:25:06,120 --> 01:25:08,748
Come on.
Grab him.

809
01:25:26,060 --> 01:25:27,771
You know where you goin' on, Miss?

810
01:25:28,855 --> 01:25:30,190
I think so.

811
01:25:30,908 --> 01:25:32,735
Thanks for your help, Mr.Nickerson.

812
01:25:32,835 --> 01:25:33,935
Yeah.

813
01:25:34,862 --> 01:25:36,164
You know...

814
01:25:37,323 --> 01:25:40,119
Bernie ain't out there, 'cause of me.
Yeah, I know.

815
01:25:41,588 --> 01:25:44,040
It's Bernie's job to go out, right?

816
01:25:47,544 --> 01:25:49,380
How can I blame me for it?

817
01:26:04,898 --> 01:26:09,153
Nice and slow! Nice and slow.
Pete, you're up next.

818
01:26:09,320 --> 01:26:12,199
Take it nice and slow! Take it easy.
Come on.

819
01:26:20,409 --> 01:26:22,752
We gotta go!
We're leavin' nobody behind.

820
01:26:22,919 --> 01:26:25,614
Go on that ladder, Eldon.
We gotta get him down.

821
01:26:25,656 --> 01:26:27,356
We have no time.

822
01:26:27,388 --> 01:26:29,850
She's slippin'.
We gotta get off this ship.

823
01:26:30,578 --> 01:26:31,880
Hurry!

824
01:26:32,055 --> 01:26:33,811
Eldon, how you doin'?

825
01:26:35,142 --> 01:26:36,936
I'm scared.

826
01:26:43,694 --> 01:26:47,406
Well...it's a lot scarier up here without us.
You gotta listen to me!

827
01:26:48,407 --> 01:26:50,763
Eldon?
We all gotta get down! Stop pushin'.

828
01:26:50,802 --> 01:26:55,866
Follow right behind me.
If I could do it, anyone can.

829
01:27:09,683 --> 01:27:10,928
Come on.

830
01:27:25,677 --> 01:27:27,677
Hold on, Eldon.

831
01:27:36,965 --> 01:27:39,593
Tiny, Tiny! Hold on.

832
01:28:36,661 --> 01:28:38,905
Eldon.

833
01:28:42,042 --> 01:28:44,837
Eldon, look at me.
Look at me.

834
01:28:57,227 --> 01:28:59,938
When I jump say, let go.
Ready?

835
01:29:07,514 --> 01:29:08,648
Jump.

836
01:29:12,996 --> 01:29:14,264
You good?

837
01:29:16,366 --> 01:29:17,666
Hold on tight.

838
01:29:23,133 --> 01:29:25,527
Alright! So heavy, you can hardly steer.

839
01:29:25,594 --> 01:29:28,547
They are saying there are
seven or eight up there aboard.

840
01:29:30,349 --> 01:29:35,731
Maybe...we take these guys back in...
come back out.

841
01:29:44,074 --> 01:29:47,995
Can't leave anybody alone.
That boat won't last.

842
01:29:50,415 --> 01:29:52,459
We all live or we all die.

843
01:29:55,171 --> 01:29:56,372
Right?

844
01:30:31,789 --> 01:30:33,750
You...aa..you did good.

845
01:30:34,600 --> 01:30:37,721
You should be last one off, Mr.Sybert.

846
01:31:36,248 --> 01:31:37,534
Last man!

847
01:33:17,618 --> 01:33:21,332
Hey Fitz! Turn off that searchlight, yeah?

848
01:33:46,402 --> 01:33:48,655
We have radio contact with the McCullough.

849
01:33:49,490 --> 01:33:54,120
I said they have lost four men, but saved the rest.
The captain of the Pollock Rip said...

850
01:33:54,287 --> 01:33:59,260
Mr.Cluff, it is 36500,
It's Bernie...right on the radio!

851
01:33:59,327 --> 01:34:03,365
Chatham, Chatham, you copy?

852
01:34:03,983 --> 01:34:08,763
CG-36500, this Station Chatham.
Webber, is that you?

853
01:34:08,929 --> 01:34:11,516
Yes, sir, it's me, Bernie.

854
01:34:12,927 --> 01:34:17,774
We got 32 survivors aboard from the Pendleton, sir.

855
01:34:18,783 --> 01:34:20,493
Station Chatham, you copy?

856
01:34:20,860 --> 01:34:26,033
36500, Station Chatham.
Did you say you have 32 survivors aboard!?

857
01:34:26,199 --> 01:34:30,747
They rescued 'em! Rescued 32 of them.
Yes sir, 32...

858
01:34:30,914 --> 01:34:34,276
We lost our compass,
so we don't know where we are...

859
01:34:34,418 --> 01:34:36,220
but we'll try to make it back home.

860
01:34:36,554 --> 01:34:38,881
Can't come back without a compass.
Not in this weather.

861
01:34:38,919 --> 01:34:40,220
They can not go back.

862
01:34:41,426 --> 01:34:43,262
You lost your compass Webber?

863
01:34:43,355 --> 01:34:47,775
No. 36500, this is the Pollock lightship.
Do not proceed to the shore.

864
01:34:48,142 --> 01:34:51,563
We're 5 miles Northeast of last
location of Pendleton.

865
01:34:51,593 --> 01:34:55,765
Proceed to our position, over.
CG-36500, Station Chatham...

866
01:34:55,969 --> 01:35:00,224
proceed to Pollock lightship
and onboard all survivors.

867
01:35:01,408 --> 01:35:03,035
What do they know, right?

868
01:35:05,580 --> 01:35:06,822
Right, Richie?

869
01:35:07,874 --> 01:35:10,294
CG-36500, you copy?

870
01:35:13,881 --> 01:35:15,391
If they know where they are...

871
01:35:16,134 --> 01:35:18,896
someone tell me where I am because
I don't know where the hell we are.

872
01:35:18,922 --> 01:35:20,749
Webber, do you copy?

873
01:35:21,349 --> 01:35:26,321
I'm not going out to sea...no.
This is Station Chatham, do you copy?

874
01:35:26,388 --> 01:35:31,911
We just got you off a boat,
there's no way we're gonna get you all up there.

875
01:35:31,978 --> 01:35:34,598
CG-36500, this is Station Chatham.

876
01:35:34,765 --> 01:35:40,747
Webber, your orders are to proceed 5 miles northeast
and onboard all survivors at the Pollock.

877
01:35:56,015 --> 01:36:00,311
Sounds like there's a cut on the radio, Mr.Cluff.
He's going at on his own.

878
01:36:01,638 --> 01:36:02,889
Bernie Webber.

879
01:36:04,558 --> 01:36:05,768
What do you know?

880
01:36:05,799 --> 01:36:07,301
How do they get home?

881
01:36:07,324 --> 01:36:09,017
He turned off his radio.

882
01:36:11,567 --> 01:36:14,403
Poor guys! I can't believe this is happening.

883
01:36:23,122 --> 01:36:24,590
There's some more stuff in the car.

884
01:36:31,515 --> 01:36:33,342
The power went out.
How do they get home?

885
01:36:33,390 --> 01:36:34,816
Powers out.

886
01:36:35,928 --> 01:36:39,057
The whole town! The powers out.

887
01:36:40,275 --> 01:36:42,903
It's worse than last year.
You never know.

888
01:37:01,258 --> 01:37:02,885
Let's get to the pier.

889
01:37:13,325 --> 01:37:15,200
How did you find us without a compass?

890
01:37:17,783 --> 01:37:21,992
We...we jodged with seasonal currents.

891
01:37:26,575 --> 01:37:28,575
Think we just got lucky.

892
01:37:28,675 --> 01:37:29,875
Yeah.

893
01:37:33,200 --> 01:37:34,442
Lucky.

894
01:37:38,075 --> 01:37:39,825
Well, you know how you get home?

895
01:37:41,200 --> 01:37:43,408
To be honest with ya, I'm not sure.

896
01:37:45,358 --> 01:37:51,325
Just, disobeyed all my ranking officers.
They don't know. So I'm better than 'em, alright?

897
01:37:52,075 --> 01:37:54,367
But the wind on my left goin' out.

898
01:37:54,825 --> 01:38:00,575
Even if I...keep it on the right,
we ought to be there in the right direction.

899
01:38:03,492 --> 01:38:07,200
We just follow all the lights on the shore.
Follow the lights on the shore.

900
01:38:20,492 --> 01:38:22,617
Well, we are in your hands, Captain.

901
01:38:32,575 --> 01:38:33,733
Listen up.

902
01:38:37,992 --> 01:38:40,075
I put the sea behind us.

903
01:38:42,033 --> 01:38:44,825
Just let it push us along,
till we land somewhere.

904
01:38:44,992 --> 01:38:50,367
Storm's easing' up boys, so..we just look
at the shore lights to guide us in.

905
01:38:50,533 --> 01:38:56,533
Even if we have to go so far as Nobska Point.
So be it! We just gonna find land!

906
01:39:01,075 --> 01:39:04,158
Been one heck of a long day, right fellas?

907
01:39:04,783 --> 01:39:07,908
Yeah, sure has!

908
01:39:09,992 --> 01:39:12,533
But don't you give up hope on me now.

909
01:39:14,742 --> 01:39:17,200
It's a good boat.
Will get us through.

910
01:39:19,617 --> 01:39:22,608
Will get you home, okay?
We are all goin' home.

911
01:39:24,242 --> 01:39:25,908
We are with you, Skipper.

912
01:42:50,575 --> 01:42:54,375
Keep the lights on, like she's doin'.
Turn your lights on.

913
01:42:54,442 --> 01:42:57,700
Turn on the lights, everyone.

914
01:42:58,367 --> 01:43:00,533
More light, so that they can see us.

915
01:43:50,283 --> 01:43:52,575
I think we made it over the bar.

916
01:43:56,117 --> 01:43:58,442
The thick tide there is over!

917
01:43:58,608 --> 01:44:01,525
You see that!?

918
01:44:23,617 --> 01:44:26,342
Fitz, turn on the searchlight.

919
01:44:57,875 --> 01:45:02,088
Look, you see that?
There are our boys!

920
01:45:13,083 --> 01:45:14,333
Is it them?

921
01:45:17,150 --> 01:45:18,758
Well done, Bernie.

922
01:45:19,283 --> 01:45:22,867
You did it, Webber!
Well done, Webber!

923
01:45:23,742 --> 01:45:26,617
36500 Chatham docking at the Chatham pier.

924
01:45:26,783 --> 01:45:31,050
Appear to be 32 survivors, sir.
I repeat: We have 32 survivors.

925
01:45:52,975 --> 01:45:54,542
Atta boy! Bernie.

926
01:46:05,375 --> 01:46:06,667
Give me the end.

927
01:46:07,617 --> 01:46:09,217
Cmon! Good to see you.
Come on over.

928
01:46:09,283 --> 01:46:11,708
Take it easy!

929
01:46:12,575 --> 01:46:16,308
This man's freezing. Give him a coat.
Go on in, it's warm inside.

930
01:46:18,283 --> 01:46:19,783
Let's get you in the lodge.

931
01:46:19,950 --> 01:46:22,250
Nice and easy. I got ya.

932
01:46:37,225 --> 01:46:38,775
Good job, Captain.

933
01:46:42,392 --> 01:46:43,725
Well done, Bernie.

934
01:46:57,005 --> 01:46:58,705
Webber?

935
01:47:25,017 --> 01:47:26,483
Bernie.

936
01:48:06,325 --> 01:48:07,833
Let's go.

937
01:48:41,167 --> 01:48:43,375
We still got 5 days until April 16.

938
01:48:43,475 --> 01:48:44,975
Yeah...

939
01:48:46,733 --> 01:48:48,575
I asked Cluff for you.

940
01:48:50,175 --> 01:48:52,442
He said it's just a...
Formality.

941
01:48:54,317 --> 01:48:56,042
Now I know, right?


